  <section>
    <h3>People:</h3>
    <p>
      From here on out, I'll just briefly pass on  the remaining categories starting with the people category. This category can handle
      GET requests for well known individuals in the game industry as well as the games that they are known for. Similar to the 
      companies category, here are the different type of GET requests available:
      <li>/people: Returns a list of all people from the database.</li>
      <li>/people/meta: Returns the meta data for the people category.</li>
      <li>/people/{personid}: Returns a person object matching the person id.</li>
      <li>/people/{personid)/games: Returns a list of games that the person has been involved with.</li>
    </p>
    <p>
      As you can see it is almost identical to the companies setup design, but simply returns different types of objects like the one
      provided below which was done with a "/people/{personid}" request:
    </p>
    <pre>
      <code>
{
  "person": {
    "id": 322,
    "name": "David DeMartini",
    "slug": "david-demartini",
    "dob": null,
    "country": null,
    "bio": null
  }
}
      </code>
    </pre>
  </section>
